g.text: START
input
Volition: You got up from this floor because of a holy vow you made sixteen years ago. With *me*. To wake up exactly 07:30 every morning until the day you die.

Electrochemistry: Speed is a potent central nervous system stimulant. It kept you propped up all day yesterday despite your debilitating hangover. How else did you think you even got up from this floor?
Electrochemistry: Fast recovery, man! Quick turnaround. Superdetective back in action.
You: What chick?
You: That's a lie. I can do this without the speed. Half the town won't be dead... (Opt out.)
speed_hangover
You: No, that's not it. *Really* I feel super-good.
You: Why is this happening?
Volition: You're too weak to say 'no' now. Waking up is the worst part. Maybe somewhere down the line you could decline...
You: I need to get more of it then. *Detecting* is my life. (Opt in.)
Volition: Don't do that. Stay strong. The hangover will wear off. You don't need to keep doing this to yourself.
Electrochemistry: Of course! Martinaise is speed-central. You just gotta poke around, follow your nose.
You: No. I can take this. I am not going to go looking for speed.
Electrochemistry: Suit yourself, slow, sad shell-man. See how you do without your spark.
You: Who am I kidding? Of course I want some speed. (Opt in.)

Electrochemistry: Are you sure? Ready to live as this pathetic shell of yourself for days? Basically a week? Let's be honest -- two weeks, maybe three? You won't make it. Half the town will be dead by then. You will be fired.
Electrochemistry: It's power, man. It's professionalism. It makes you feel like you're young again and ready to *detect*! Ready to go to war against the world!
You: Is that how it's going to be now when I close my eyes?
Electrochemistry: Oh, just a dream. You have ones like that all the time. You feel even worse this morning than you did last night.
You: I think Cuno might have speed. I should ask him and start blasting again. (Opt in.)
Electrochemistry: Yes. Wait till you see the one with the chick in it, it's gonna be a good one. You feel even worse this morning than you did last night.
why_is_speed
Electrochemistry: You mean why are you so tired? Too tired and *down* to even think? It *is* worrying, isn't it. You can't be a detective like this -- detectives need to be able to think.
speedhub
Electrochemistry: That's not really true. Your heart has finally pumped all the *speed* out of your system, buster. Time to get some more.
Electrochemistry: Good going, buddy.
Variable["whirling.speed_volition"]
Variable["whirling.speed_volition"]
Electrochemistry: Really? Because you feel even worse this morning than you did last night.
!(Variable["whirling.speed_volition"])
Electrochemistry: It's just that your heart has finally pumped all the *speed* out of your system, buster. Time to get some more.
Electrochemistry: Don't be silly. There was no vow. You were high on speed. That was the only reason you got up. You can't *detect* without it, it's that simple.
You: Oh my god, what the hell was that...
Electrochemistry: You don't know? Some broad that messed you up. It'll come to you. It always does.
Electrochemistry: You and speed will be happy again. You will make her come home. This time it will be different.
You: What the hell is going on with me?
You: I just had the most beautiful dream. Uplifting. Rejuvenating.
Variable["whirling.speed_volition"]
Variable["whirling.speed_volition"]
!(Variable["whirling.speed_volition"])
You: Wait. What *is*... speed?
